A cure that's supposed to be voluntary.

128
00:05:43,447 --> 00:05:46,329
How can Kramer just force
Frost to take it like that?

129
00:05:46,332 --> 00:05:48,506
- Is that even legal?
- Yeah, you would be surprised

130
00:05:48,509 --> 00:05:50,552
what can become legal when
you've got the full force

131
00:05:50,554 --> 00:05:52,653
of the American justice
system behind you.

132
00:05:52,656 --> 00:05:54,643
It can be pretty scary sometimes.

133
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:59,082
What if we forget the deal,
just take the 10 to 20 years?

134
00:05:59,084 --> 00:06:01,694
Prosecution's not even
seeking jail time anymore.

135
00:06:01,696 --> 00:06:03,217
Kramer is all about the cure.

136
00:06:03,219 --> 00:06:06,046
She wants Frost neutralized forever.

137
00:06:06,049 --> 00:06:07,614
At least it can't get any worse.

138
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:09,851
Actually, it can.

139
00:06:09,854 --> 00:06:11,921
I just talked to Mom. She's
gonna run some more tests

140
00:06:11,923 --> 00:06:14,620
to be sure, but we think
that because you are

141
00:06:14,622 --> 00:06:18,232
uniquely born from meta
DNA, if you take the cure...

142
00:06:18,234 --> 00:06:20,539
It could harm you, maybe even kill you.

143
00:06:20,541 --> 00:06:24,151
This is insane. Okay,
no one is touching Frost.

144
00:06:24,153 --> 00:06:26,075
- We're gonna stop this, right?
- Hell yeah.

145
00:06:26,078 --> 00:06:28,460
Okay, we need to fight fire with fire.

146
00:06:28,462 --> 00:06:29,722
Hack Kramer, dig up dirt,

147
00:06:29,724 --> 00:06:31,497
whatever it takes to save Frost.

148
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,640
