262
00:11:49,696 --> 00:11:51,565
No, I wasn't.

263
00:11:51,567 --> 00:11:54,655
Okay, look, this is a huge scoop for me.

264
00:11:54,657 --> 00:11:57,181
Could you just give me ten minutes?

265
00:11:59,619 --> 00:12:01,195
How much time do I have left

266
00:12:01,198 --> 00:12:02,676
before the cameras turn back on?

267
00:12:02,679 --> 00:12:04,795
20 seconds. We have to
deliver the oximeter now

268
00:12:04,798 --> 00:12:06,754
or we're screwed.

269
00:12:06,756 --> 00:12:09,085
Please, if I go back empty-handed,

270
00:12:09,088 --> 00:12:10,802
my boss is gonna kill me.

271
00:12:10,804 --> 00:12:12,891
Ten minutes, that's all I'm asking.

272
00:12:12,893 --> 00:12:19,724
♪

273
00:12:19,726 --> 00:12:21,421
You've got five.

274
00:12:21,423 --> 00:12:23,555
Thanks. Let's go sit.

275
00:12:31,389 --> 00:12:34,303
Whoa, you should really
get that checked out.

276
00:12:34,313 --> 00:12:37,752
Yeah, I'll have someone
take a look at it.

277
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,580
Ten seconds, go, go, go, go!

278
00:12:42,705 --> 00:12:45,706
[energized music]

279
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:51,669
♪

280
00:12:51,671 --> 00:12:53,375
The cure has been neutralized.

281
00:12:53,378 --> 00:12:57,179
Now get the hell out of there
before I have a heart attack.

282
00:12:59,642 --> 00:13:02,036
Yeah!

283
00:13:06,903 --> 00:13:10,470
Wait... so, am I under arrest?

284
00:13:10,472 --> 00:13:11,732
No, no, no, no.

285
00:13:11,734 --> 00:13:13,691
I... I am with CCPD,

286
00:13:13,693 --> 00:13:15,127
but I... I'm a CSI,

287
00:13:15,129 --> 00:13:17,004
I... I don't arrest people.

288
00:13:17,007 --> 00:13:19,914
But you think I'm guilty of something.

289
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:23,265
[scoffs] Right.

290
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:25,311
Never gonna catch a break, am I?

291
00:13:25,313 --> 00:13:27,052
I'm sorry, I don't follow.

292
00:13:27,054 --> 00:13:28,270
Okay, fine.

293
00:13:28,272 --> 00:13:30,055
Yeah, it's true, I was an addict.

294
00:13:30,057 --> 00:13:33,129
Then I hit rock bottom,
and that was a wake-up call.

295
00:13:33,132 --> 00:13:35,984
So I got clean, I went to school.

296
00:13:35,987 --> 00:13:37,366
I could have worked in a hospital,

297
00:13:37,368 --> 00:13:39,238
but this is where I belong.

298
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,938
Helping people, just like
me, turn their lives around.

299
00:13:44,468 --> 00:13:46,811
Look, I've been to rehab,
and I don't have a record,

300
00:13:46,813 --> 00:13:48,377
so whatever crime
you're investigating...

301
00:13:48,379 --> 00:13:50,728
No, no, it's... it's...
it's nothing like that.

302
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:52,166
Um... uh, we...

303
00:13:54,036 --> 00:13:56,167
Um... [clears throat]

304
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:58,257
It's... it's gonna sound

305
00:13:58,259 --> 00:14:01,093
kind of crazy, but we've
been scanning the city

306
00:14:01,096 --> 00:14:04,077
for a new meta, and for some reason

307
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,617
our readings led us to you.

308
00:14:07,903 --> 00:14:10,208
Seriously?

309
00:14:10,211 --> 00:14:12,907
I'm not a meta.

310
00:14:12,910 --> 00:14:15,737
We're not so sure.

311
00:14:15,740 --> 00:14:18,262
Well, then what do you want from me?

312
00:14:18,265 --> 00:14:20,414
Alexa, we'd like for you to come to

313
00:14:20,417 --> 00:14:23,108
S.T.A.R. Labs with us.
We work with a team there

314
00:14:23,110 --> 00:14:24,936
that can conduct a
simple, painless test...

315
00:14:24,938 --> 00:14:26,468
Tell us what we already know.

316
00:14:26,471 --> 00:14:28,417
That you're the monster
who attacked Central City

317
00:14:28,419 --> 00:14:31,029
and killed a man and
tried to kill me too.

318
00:14:31,031 --> 00:14:33,509
I have never seen you before in my life,

319
00:14:33,511 --> 00:14:34,815
and I'm not going anywhere with you,

320
00:14:34,817 --> 00:14:37,296
especially not S.T.A.R. Labs.

321
00:14:37,298 --> 00:14:39,733
Yeah, I've heard of them.
They're the ones who started

322
00:14:39,735 --> 00:14:41,213
all this meta stuff in the first place.

323
00:14:41,215 --> 00:14:42,605
Alexa, hold on, we just want to help.

324
00:14:42,607 --> 00:14:44,564
No, you hold on.

325
00:14:44,566 --> 00:14:46,958
I am not a monster.

326
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,655
And if you don't mind,

327
00:14:48,657 --> 00:14:51,745
there are people who
actually need my help.

328
00:14:51,747 --> 00:14:53,812
Please don't contact me again.

329
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:04,700
I don't see why you're so upset.

330
00:15:04,703 --> 00:15:05,890
We know that woman

331
00:15:05,892 --> 00:15:07,108
is the thing we've been searching for.

332
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:08,992
No, we think she might be.

333
00:15:08,995 --> 00:15:10,372
But now we'll never learn the truth,

334
00:15:10,374 --> 00:15:12,070
because you scared her away.

335
00:15:12,072 --> 00:15:14,969
Barry, the answer is simple.
If she won't come to us,

336
00:15:14,972 --> 00:15:16,842
- we'll make her.
- What?

337
00:15:16,845 --> 00:15:18,497
We move in the blink of an eye.

338
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,818
She'll never know, and
by the time she does,

339
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:23,429
we'll test her, and...
if she's innocent,

340
00:15:23,431 --> 00:15:25,344
return her before she
takes her next breath.

341
00:15:25,346 --> 00:15:27,085
Nora, I know you're new to all this,

342
00:15:27,087 --> 00:15:28,521
but we don't just grab people

343
00:15:28,523 --> 00:15:29,516
and test them against their will.

344
00:15:29,518 --> 00:15:30,781
- Why not?
- Because...

345
00:15:30,784 --> 00:15:32,477
- Lives are at stake.
- That's not how this works.

346
00:15:32,479 --> 00:15:34,320
Well, maybe it should.

347
00:15:34,323 --> 00:15:37,181
Barry, you and I know what
this thing is really capable of.

348
00:15:37,184 --> 00:15:39,097
Now, all I'm asking
is for you to trust me

349
00:15:39,099 --> 00:15:40,820
and do what needs to be done.

350
00:15:40,823 --> 00:15:42,361
Is that really too much for me to ask?

351
00:15:42,363 --> 00:15:43,666
You're asking him to give up

352
00:15:43,668 --> 00:15:45,407
a part of what makes hima hero.

353
00:15:45,409 --> 00:15:48,889
So, yes, Nora, it is too much.

354
00:15:48,891 --> 00:15:51,241
Barry.

355
00:15:52,808 --> 00:15:54,460
It's your choice.

356
00:15:54,462 --> 00:15:57,463
[tense music]

357
00:15:57,465 --> 00:16:02,033
♪

358
00:16:02,035 --> 00:16:03,991
Captain West,

359
00:16:03,993 --> 00:16:07,168
you're here to make a statement
on behalf of the Defendant.

360
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:08,345
If you please?

361
00:16:10,304 --> 00:16:11,968
I admit, under oath,

362
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:16,089
that Frost hasn't always been
on the right side of the law.

363
00:16:16,092 --> 00:16:18,745
But I can also say

364
00:16:18,747 --> 00:16:21,139
that she has put her life on the line

365
00:16:21,141 --> 00:16:24,153
countless times to save others.

366
00:16:24,156 --> 00:16:26,840
How so, Captain?

367
00:16:26,842 --> 00:16:29,974
Frost has fought alongside
Earth's greatest heroes

368
00:16:29,976 --> 00:16:31,497
to save the world, which means

369
00:16:31,499 --> 00:16:34,848
that she's saved every
person in this room

370
00:16:34,850 --> 00:16:37,459
including those who want to lock her up

371
00:16:37,461 --> 00:16:40,985
for being who she was.

372
00:16:40,987 --> 00:16:45,076
Not for who she is today.

373
00:16:45,078 --> 00:16:47,687
And,

374
00:16:47,689 --> 00:16:50,603
Your Honor...

375
00:16:50,605 --> 00:16:54,520
I don't understand how this court

376
00:16:54,522 --> 00:16:59,090
can force Frost to take that cure

377
00:16:59,092 --> 00:17:03,181
without sacrificing
what it stands for...

378
00:17:03,183 --> 00:17:04,749
Justice.

379
00:17:08,405 --> 00:17:10,666
Thank you, Captain West.

380
00:17:10,668 --> 00:17:12,932
Your word goes a long way in this court.

381
00:17:14,281 --> 00:17:16,109
[mouthing]

382
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:19,195
In fact,

383
00:17:19,198 --> 00:17:21,853
I believe I'm ready
to deliver my verdict.

384
00:17:24,204 --> 00:17:25,632
Your Honor.

385
00:17:25,635 --> 00:17:27,813
We have a new update
regarding a relevant incident

386
00:17:27,816 --> 00:17:29,507
that could affect your ruling.

387
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:31,293
If it pleases the court.

388
00:17:31,296 --> 00:17:33,167
Proceed.

389
00:17:33,169 --> 00:17:35,122
Earlier today, the
meta-human cure supply

390
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:37,426
at CCPD was rendered inert.

391
00:17:37,429 --> 00:17:41,262
It is now completely unusable.

392
00:17:41,264 --> 00:17:44,483
The State suspects foul play
by the only person with motive

393
00:17:44,485 --> 00:17:46,957
for such bold treachery... Killer Frost.

394
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,530
No, I didn't do it.

395
00:17:48,532 --> 00:17:50,960
It wasn't me, I have not been to CCPD.

396
00:17:50,963 --> 00:17:53,137
- I've been here!
- Let me handle this, please.

397
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,981
Objection. Your Honor, this
is speculative nonsense.

398
00:17:55,984 --> 00:17:57,539
Sustained.

399
00:17:57,541 --> 00:18:00,325
Prosecutor, do you have
evidence for your accusations?

400
00:18:00,327 --> 00:18:02,370
Yes, Your Honor.

401
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:04,459
CCPD security cameras were hacked at

402
00:18:04,461 --> 00:18:06,679
the exact moment the cure was destroyed.

403
00:18:06,681 --> 00:18:08,289
We wouldn't have found out if not for

404
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:10,988
Ms. Kramer's expertise
in military intelligence.

405
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:13,427
She uncovered the hack herself.

406
00:18:18,214 --> 00:18:20,519
It was me, Your Honor.

407
00:18:20,521 --> 00:18:22,956
I did it, not Frost. And I acted alone.

408
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:24,479
She's lying, Your Honor.

409
00:18:24,481 --> 00:18:26,307
Killer Frost is clearly
behind this crime,

410
00:18:26,309 --> 00:18:27,613
because her criminal past is

411
00:18:27,615 --> 00:18:28,641
the same as her criminal present.

412
00:18:28,643 --> 00:18:30,808
I am not a criminal, what is
wrong with her, she keeps...

413
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:32,842
- [overlapping arguing]
- Order.

414
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:35,106
I said order.

415
00:18:35,109 --> 00:18:37,103
Everybody sit down.

416
00:18:38,538 --> 00:18:43,437
Now, Ms. Strong, considering
the cure isn't a viable option,

417
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,109
can the court assume
the State is no longer

418
00:18:45,111 --> 00:18:46,914
seeking it as a punishment?

419
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:48,460
On the contrary.

420
00:18:48,462 --> 00:18:51,463
[tense music]

421
00:18:51,465 --> 00:18:53,813
♪

422
00:18:53,815 --> 00:18:55,887
And where exactly did you get that?

423
00:18:55,890 --> 00:18:58,122
My colleague Ms. Kramer
knows the magnitude of

424
00:18:58,124 --> 00:18:59,819
the meta-criminal we are dealing with.

425
00:18:59,821 --> 00:19:02,691
So, she contacted A.R.G.U.S.
on behalf of the State

426
00:19:02,693 --> 00:19:06,739
and had them replicate the
cure based on CCPD samples.

427
00:19:06,741 --> 00:19:10,047
We should have 100
vials ready by nightfall.

428
00:19:10,049 --> 00:19:13,615
All we need is your
decision, Your Honor.

429
00:19:13,617 --> 00:19:16,009
Very well.

430
00:19:16,011 --> 00:19:18,751
I'll retire to my chambers
and make my decision.

431
00:19:18,753 --> 00:19:21,145
Court is adjourned.

432
00:19:21,147 --> 00:19:23,147
All rise.

433
00:19:23,149 --> 00:19:26,150
[suspenseful music]

434
00:19:26,152 --> 00:19:31,757
♪

435
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,718
This is for your own good.

436
00:19:37,337 --> 00:19:40,642
What just happened?

437
00:19:40,644 --> 00:19:43,776
We just lost.

438
00:19:43,778 --> 00:19:47,869
[dramatic music]

439
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:53,351
Babe?

440
00:19:53,353 --> 00:19:56,182
Please, tell us you
know a way out of this.

441
00:20:00,403 --> 00:20:02,640
I'm sorry, but...

442
00:20:02,643 --> 00:20:04,948
I don't.

443
00:20:04,951 --> 00:20:07,190
I don't know... I don't know
how we're gonna keep Frost

444
00:20:07,193 --> 00:20:09,193
from being forced to take the cure.

445
00:20:09,195 --> 00:20:10,796
What's Kramer's deal, anyway?

446
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:13,109
Kramer's had it out for me
since before I was arrested.

447
00:20:13,112 --> 00:20:15,648
My gut tells me she's
still hiding something.

448
00:20:15,651 --> 00:20:17,330
We need a miracle, and fast.

449
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,290
No, we don't. Because
we are Team Flash,

450
00:20:19,292 --> 00:20:21,770
and we have more than enough
resources to figure this out.

451
00:20:21,772 --> 00:20:23,552
Caitlin, we already went
that route, remember?

452
00:20:23,554 --> 00:20:25,165
And all we did was make things worse.

453
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,776
Okay, well I can't just sit
here and do nothing, okay?

454
00:20:27,778 --> 00:20:29,070
Because Frost is my sister,

455
00:20:29,073 --> 00:20:31,815
and I have to do everything
I can to protect her.

456
00:20:33,784 --> 00:20:36,002
Guys, I need to talk to Caitlin.

457
00:20:36,004 --> 00:20:38,180
Alone.

458
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:56,484
You want to explain yourself?

459
00:20:56,487 --> 00:20:58,070
Caity, you made me a promise

460
00:20:58,073 --> 00:21:00,200
that we would fight
this the way I wanted to.

461
00:21:00,202 --> 00:21:01,593
Okay, but that's the thing, okay...

462
00:21:01,595 --> 00:21:03,247
You are not fighting this.

463
00:21:03,249 --> 00:21:05,481
You skipped your trial, and
look how that turned out.

464
00:21:05,484 --> 00:21:07,863
And whose fault is that?

465
00:21:09,733 --> 00:21:12,908
[phone buzzes]

466
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:14,723
It's Mom, she got the test results back

467
00:21:14,726 --> 00:21:18,218
from how the cure will
affect your meta-DNA.

468
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:20,070
Thank God, she says you'll be fine.

469
00:21:20,073 --> 00:21:21,724
The cure will take away your powers,

470
00:21:21,727 --> 00:21:25,007
but it won't harm you...
You're gonna survive.

471
00:21:26,228 --> 00:21:27,793
Great, whatever.

472
00:21:27,795 --> 00:21:31,536
Frost, this is the miracle
we've been waiting for.

473
00:21:31,538 --> 00:21:33,190
This is gonna save you.

474
00:21:33,192 --> 00:21:35,366
By erasing my powers?

475
00:21:35,368 --> 00:21:37,194
You heard Cecile, okay.

476
00:21:37,196 --> 00:21:41,328
Even if we can convince the
judge to give you prison time,

477
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:43,330
you're looking at 10 to 20 years easy.

478
00:21:43,332 --> 00:21:45,158
Then I'll take it.

479
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:48,074
Why would you give up
two decades of your life

480
00:21:48,076 --> 00:21:50,250
when there is a perfectly safe solution?

481
00:21:50,252 --> 00:21:53,166
Changing who I am is not a solution.

482
00:21:53,168 --> 00:21:55,248
How the hell can you even ask me that?

483
00:21:55,251 --> 00:21:57,817
You're the one who said the
cure should always be a choice.

484
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:00,260
Then why won't you choose this?

485
00:22:00,262 --> 00:22:03,263
[solemn music]

486
00:22:03,265 --> 00:22:04,875
I...

487
00:22:07,125 --> 00:22:09,226
Do you remember when
the Sage Force attacked,

488
00:22:09,228 --> 00:22:12,272
and I told you my greatest fear?

489
00:22:12,274 --> 00:22:16,276
It's living life without you.

490
00:22:16,278 --> 00:22:21,542
I am terrified of living
a life that you're not in.

491
00:22:21,544 --> 00:22:25,154
Frost, you are my sister, I love you.

492
00:22:25,156 --> 00:22:27,546
And I cannot lose you.

493
00:22:29,725 --> 00:22:32,117
And if I take the cure, you will.

494
00:22:34,253 --> 00:22:36,775
Caity, don't you see?

495
00:22:36,777 --> 00:22:39,299
It's not me you trying to protect.

496
00:22:39,301 --> 00:22:41,519
It's yourself.

497
00:22:41,521 --> 00:22:48,571
♪

498
00:22:59,278 --> 00:23:01,234
[whoosh]

499
00:23:01,236 --> 00:23:02,542
The Flash.

500
00:23:05,545 --> 00:23:08,894
That CSI sent you, didn't he?

501
00:23:08,896 --> 00:23:10,918
Alexa, I know everything
you've heard today

502
00:23:10,921 --> 00:23:15,335
probably sounds insane,
let alone terrifying.

503
00:23:15,337 --> 00:23:19,121
But, if you give me a chance,
I think maybe I can explain

504
00:23:19,123 --> 00:23:23,212
why it's so important you get tested.

505
00:23:23,214 --> 00:23:25,389
I already know why.

506
00:23:25,391 --> 00:23:28,392
[somber music]

507
00:23:28,394 --> 00:23:34,572
♪

508
00:23:34,574 --> 00:23:39,751
[Fuerza roars]

509
00:23:39,753 --> 00:23:42,265
You were there when Fuerza
attacked Central City.

510
00:23:45,498 --> 00:23:47,585
I was part of a team

511
00:23:47,587 --> 00:23:50,979
building low income housing that week.

512
00:23:50,981 --> 00:23:55,070
And I just remember feeling so angry

513
00:23:55,072 --> 00:23:57,945
when Abra Kadabra
destroyed our worksite.

514
00:24:00,687 --> 00:24:03,342
But I don't remember much else.

515
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:09,824
I've been having, um...

516
00:24:09,826 --> 00:24:12,261
blackouts.

517
00:24:12,263 --> 00:24:15,700
Just waking up in strange
places, not knowing...

518
00:24:15,702 --> 00:24:18,442
where I've been, or...

519
00:24:18,444 --> 00:24:21,183
Or what I've done.

520
00:24:21,185 --> 00:24:23,882
When's the last time it happened?

521
00:24:23,884 --> 00:24:27,189
When this thing attacked.

522
00:24:27,191 --> 00:24:29,453
What if I...

523
00:24:29,455 --> 00:24:32,630
Oh, my God, what if I am this monster?

524
00:24:32,632 --> 00:24:34,936
Help me find out.

525
00:24:34,938 --> 00:24:36,764
Trust me,

526
